The article discusses the negative impact of Obamacare on healthcare in the United States. It mentions that premiums have risen and continue to rise, millions remain uninsured, and insurance providers are leaving the market. The article features videos from Tonya Horton, who owns a medical instrument and billing company, and Dr. Thomas Little, a cardiologist, who share their experiences of the waste and suffering caused by Obamacare. The article concludes by stating that without action to repeal and replace Obamacare, Americans will face higher costs, more taxes, and fewer choices in healthcare.